            "doi": "10.1371/journal.pcbi.1003494",
            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "We show that existing RNA-seq, DNase-seq, and ChIP-seq data exhibit overdispersed per-base read count distributions that are not matched to existing computational method assumptions. To compensate for this overdispersion we introduce a nonparametric and universal method for processing per-base sequencing read count data called FIXSEQ. We demonstrate that FIXSEQ substantially improves the performance of existing RNA-seq, DNase-seq, and ChIP-seq analysis tools when compared with existing alternatives. \u00a9 2014 Hashimoto et al.",
